@startuml
title Viaverse Release / Rollback / Migration — State Diagram

[*] --> DRAFT
DRAFT --> CI_RUNNING : PR merge/tag
CI_RUNNING --> BLOCKED : gate failed
CI_RUNNING --> READY_TO_DEPLOY : gates passed
BLOCKED --> CI_RUNNING : fix + rerun
READY_TO_DEPLOY --> MIGRATING : predeploy migration
MIGRATING --> DEPLOYING : migration ok
DEPLOYING --> VERIFYING : rollout done
VERIFYING --> RELEASED : healthy
VERIFYING --> ROLLBACK_REQUIRED : bad health/SLO
ROLLBACK_REQUIRED --> ROLLED_BACK : previous version

RELEASED --> [*]
ROLLED_BACK --> [*]

note bottom
Rollback must be tested, but DB migrations may not be trivially reversible.
Prefer expand-contract migrations for safety.
end note
@enduml
